(v) 

Recordkeeping.



(A) Each owner or operator of a facility which is subject to the limitations of paragraphs (b)(1)(iii)(B) 

(1) 

through 

(5) 

of this section, as described under paragraphs (b)(1)(ii) (A) or (B) of this section shall collect and record all information
necessary to demonstrate compliance with the limitations of paragraphs (b)(1)(iii)(B) 

(1) 

through 

(5) 

of this section for each emissions source and maintain the information at the facility for a period of five (5) years.
The information shall be collected and recorded each day of each calendar year beginning in 2001 and ending with 2005.


(B) Each owner or operator of a facility which is exempt from the limitations of paragraphs (b)(1)(iii)(B) 

(1)

 through 

(5)

 of this section, as described under paragraph (b)(1)(ii)(C) of this section shall collect and record all information
necessary to demonstrate that actual emissions of VOC from all emissions sources are less than 6.8 kg (15 lbs) during
each day and maintain the information at the facility for a period of five (5) years. The information shall be collected
and recorded each day of each calendar year beginning in 2001 and ending with 2005. 

